cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with the problem of reconstructing packet arrival rates and counts in a communication network, which involves signal processing and network analysis. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also involves the use of compressed sensing, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of expander graphs and sparse matrices suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
